  "title": "STUDENT CARE TEACHERS (ISLANDWIDE LOCATIONS AVAILABLE)",
  "description": "<p><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Plan and conduct both indoor and outdoor activities for primary school students</li>\n  <li>Ensure students' welfare and safety are being taken care of</li>\n  <li>Supervise students to ensure completion of homework and that spelling revision is done</li>\n  <li>Liaise with parents and form teachers to provide feedback on students' behavioural and learning progress</li>\n  <li>Handle administrative duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min. GCE “O” level and above</li>\n  <li>Able to lead and manage primary school students</li>\n  <li>Able to communicate well with parents and students</li>\n  <li>Some relevant working experience in a related field</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>WORKING HOURS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Normal school term working hours: 11am - 7pm (Mon - Fri)</li>\n  <li>School holiday working hours: 8-hour shift between 7.30am to 7pm (Mon - Fri)</li>\n</ul>",
